`issue:` RenderQueue::sort use an unstable_sort algorithm will cause render re-order for Android.
`reproduce:`SpriteTest->Testing Sprite

``` cpp
void Sprite1::addNewSpriteWithCoords(Vec2 p)
{
    int idx = (int)(CCRANDOM_0_1() * 1400.0f / 100.0f);
    int x = (idx%5) * 85;
    int y = (idx/5) * 121;
    auto sprite = Sprite::create("Images/grossini_dance_atlas.png", Rect(x,y,85,121) );
    addChild( sprite );
    sprite->setGlobalZOrder(10);
    sprite->setPosition( Vec2( p.x, p.y) );
}
```

I'm not sure if this is an issue or a design "feature" that needs change of documentation.

Because we'd have to check for visibility in many many places in our own code everywhere we have an "on" event based on scene graph priority I believe this is an issue and not a valid API or Engine change.

Our solution

``` cpp
/// CCEventDispatcher.cpp : Line 843
Camera::_visitingCamera = camera;
for (auto& l : sceneListeners)
{
    auto lCameraMask = l->getAssociatedNode()->getCameraMask();
    auto cameraFlag = (unsigned short)camera->getCameraFlag();
    auto canVisitFlag = ((cameraFlag & lCameraMask) != 0);
    // NOTE: protected
    //auto canVisit = l->getAssociatedNode()->isVisitableByVisitingCamera();
    auto canVisit = canVisitFlag;
    if (canVisit && onEvent(l))
    {
        shouldStopPropagation = true;
        break;
    }
}
```
